    "nootropics_101_qRn6wC": {
      "type": "nootropics-101",
      "blocks": {
        "qa_QadKm4": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What Are Nootropics?",
            "answer": "<p>Nootropics are nutrients, plant extracts and synthetics that support aspects of cognition such as focus, attention, memory, motivation and stress resilience. </p><p>They are not a single drug class. </p><p>Common groups include cholinergics (for example <a href=\"/products/alpha-gpc-250mg-capsules\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Alpha-GPC 250mg Capsules\">Alpha-GPC</a> and <a href=\"/products/cdp-choline-250mg-capsules\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"CDP-choline 250mg Capsules\">CDP-Choline</a>), amino acids (<a href=\"/products/l-theanine-200mg-capsules\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"L-Theanine 200mg Capsules\">L-Theanine</a>, <a href=\"/products/n-acetyl-l-tyrosine-350mg-capsules\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"N-Acetyl L-Tyrosine 350mg Capsules\">N-Acetyl-L-Tyrosine</a>), adaptogens (Rhodiola, <a href=\"/products/lion-mane-mushroom-capsules\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lion's Mane 500mg Capsules\">Lion’s Mane</a>) and <a href=\"/collections/racetams\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Racetams\">racetams</a>. </p><p>As with any supplement, quality and dosing matter. </p><p>Look for products made in cGMP facilities with third-party testing to verify identity, potency and purity. </p><p>Results vary by individual and goal, and no product is a substitute for sleep, nutrition, hydration and movement. </p><p>If you are new, start with one simple, well-studied ingredient and evaluate how you feel over a couple of weeks before adding anything else.</p><p></p><p></p>",
            "icon": "brain",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "cta_label": "Read the Beginner’s Guide",
            "cta_url": "shopify://pages/guides-beginners-nootropics",
            "anchor": "what-are-nootropics"
          }
        },
        "qa_zyG3tE": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How Should I Start?",
            "answer": "<p>Start with one clear goal—<a href=\"/collections/focus\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Focus\">focus</a>, <a href=\"/collections/calm\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Calm\">calm</a>, <a href=\"/collections/memory\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Memory\">memory</a>, <a href=\"/collections/energy\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Energy\">energy</a>, or <a href=\"/collections/sleep\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Sleep\">sleep</a>. </p><p>Choose a single ingredient that matches it and keep the rest of your routine steady so you can observe changes. </p><p>Take the lowest effective serving on the label at the same time each day for 7–14 days, then adjust only if needed. </p><p>New users often begin with non‑stim options such as <a href=\"/products/l-theanine-200mg-capsules\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"L-Theanine 200mg Capsules\">L‑Theanine</a> (calm focus) or <a href=\"/products/lion-mane-mushroom-powder\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lion Mane Mushroom Powder\">Lion’s Mane</a> (learning support). </p><p>If you use stimulants, be mindful of timing and sensitivity. </p><p>Track simple notes on sleep, mood, and productivity; one change at a time beats big overhauls. </p><p>Prefer a shortcut? </p><p>Use our quick quiz to get a small, evidence‑informed starter stack tailored to your goal and sensitivity.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p>",
            "icon": "brain",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "cta_label": "Read the beginner’s guide",
            "cta_url": "",
            "anchor": ""
          }
        },
        "qa_iRatqr": {
          "type": "qa",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is Stacking?",
            "answer": "<p>“Stacking” means combining complementary ingredients to target a goal. </p><p>Aim for synergy, not size—two or three well‑chosen compounds usually beat a long list. </p><p>Keep roles clear (for example, a focus driver paired with a smoothing co‑pilot) and add only one change at a time. </p><p>Many people pair <a href=\"/products/caffeine-l-theanine-capsules\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Caffeine L-Theanine Capsules\">caffeine with L‑Theanine</a> for calm alertness, or add a choline source (<a href=\"/products/alpha-gpc-250mg-capsules\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Alpha-GPC 250mg Capsules\">Alpha‑GPC</a> or <a href=\"/products/cdp-choline-250mg-capsules\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"CDP-choline 250mg Capsules\">CDP‑Choline</a>) with racetams. </p><p>Space stimulating ingredients earlier in the day and cycle or take rest days if tolerance builds for you. </p><p>Track how you feel and sleep, and pause if anything feels off. </p><p>If you prefer plug‑and‑play, start with a simple <a href=\"/collections/stacks\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Stacks\">pre‑built stack</a> designed for your goal; you can always swap ingredients as you learn your response.</p><p><br/></p>",
            "icon": "brain",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "cta_label": "Shop Pre‑Built Stacks",
            "cta_url": "shopify://collections/stacks",
            "anchor": "stacking-basics"
          }
        }
      },
